<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="sans-serif" COLOR="#FFFFFF"><b>Aanadil</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B>Non-Member</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Joined: Jan 12, 2002</FONT><br><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Posts: 3</FONT></td><TD><img src="/phpBB/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Posted: 2002-03-14 03:56&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF" face="sans-serif">Mike, and other old friends,<BR><BR>    What a crazy few months. Well, I must say that Untamed Dreamers had done pretty well, we were clipping along and growing, and also growing smarter, I was pixels away from level 55, when events all came to a head and i realized something that deeply bothered me.<BR><BR>    This game really sucks! It sucks the life, honesty, integrity and loyalty right out of you. I watched people I have been friends with for ages argue with one another about drops, question the way that they spent their in game time, and become blatantly calloused to one another, all the time forgetting that this is just a game, then it dawned on me, I was, and had been the same sort of heartless fool, sigh. Took a while for me to reralize how genuinely selfish and insensitive this game was making me, but upon the revelation of it, as well as the RL truth that a lvl 55 toon plays waaaay too much, I gave my gear to Basil, and deleted my characters one by one before closing my accounts. Thus unsuring that the addictive power would never pull me back in.<BR><BR>    I am happy that I got a chance to start UD, it was truly a blast, and I loved the new experiences, but I hated how addicted I had become to this Game, and the line of Bruised Freindships. I appologize to you here for what I allowed it to do to our friendship. <BR><BR>                     Scott</FONT><BR>
